The paper focuses on multi-agent systems and game theoretic learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Additionally, the paper proposes enhancements to two types of learning algorithms, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of game theory also suggests the sub-category of cs.GT (Game Theory). Finally, the paper mentions applications in robotics, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics).
